### Get a Specific Response [GET /response/<response_id>]
Used to get one response. All you have to do is use the given endpoind `/response/` and append the `response_id` to the end of the `URL`.
+ Response 200 (application/json)
{

    "date": "2016-08-06",
    "id": 55,
    "modules": [ ],
    "resource_uri": "/api/full/response/55/",
    "tags": [ ],
    "text": "Ants in my eyes Johnson",
    "time": "22:19:37",
    "timezone": "UTC",
    "votes": [ ]

}

### Create a New Response [POST]

You may create your own response using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing a response.

**NOTE:**  The `Authorization` header must be set in the format: `Authorization: ApiKey <username>:<api_key>`.
+ Parameters
  - text (string) - The text of the response.
  - question_id (integer) - The id of the associated question.
  - modules (string<json>, optional) - Used to add a bunch of modules. The string should be a json array, beginning with `[` and ending with `]`. Should be a list of `module` `POST` data.
+ Headers
  Authorization: ApiKey daniel:204db7bcfafb2deb7506b89eb3b9b715b09905c8
+ Request (application/json)
  + Data
        {
            "text": "This is definatly a response",
            "question_id": 50
            "modules": [
              {
                "title": "test module title",
                "text": "text module text"
              },
              {
                "title": "this is the second module title",
                "text": "this is the second module text"
              }
            ]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /responses/55

    + Body

